## Project: cargo-dist (dist)

Shippable application packaging for Rust. Builds binaries, generates installers (shell, PowerShell, Homebrew, npm, MSI, macOS .pkg), and creates CI pipelines for automated releases.

## Workspace Crates

- `cargo-dist/` — Main CLI + library (binary: `dist`). All core logic lives here.
- `cargo-dist-schema/` — JSON schema for `dist-manifest.json` (the machine-readable release manifest).
- `axoproject/` — Workspace discovery: reads Cargo, npm, and generic project metadata.

## Language & Toolchain

- Rust edition 2021, MSRV 1.74, toolchain 1.93
- Uses first-party `axo*` crates: axoasset (file I/O), axocli (CLI), axoprocess (subprocesses), axotag (git tags), axoupdater (self-update)

## Code Conventions

- `#![deny(missing_docs)]` — all public items need doc comments
- Use `camino::Utf8Path` / `Utf8PathBuf` instead of `std::path`
- Use `miette` for error reporting, `thiserror` for error definitions, `DistResult<T>` as return type
- Use `tracing` for logging (not `println!` or `log`)
- Use `axoprocess::Cmd` instead of `std::process::Command`
- Use `axoasset::LocalAsset` for file operations
- Clippy allows: `single_match`, `result_large_err`

## Architecture

Core pipeline in `cargo-dist/src/`:
- `tasks.rs` — Central planner. `gather_work()` builds the `DistGraph` (releases, variants, artifacts, build steps).
- `config/` — Config parsing. v0 (Cargo.toml metadata) and v1 (dist-workspace.toml) formats, with migration support.
- `build/` — Build execution: cargo builds, generic builds, fake/mock builds for testing.
- `backend/ci/` — CI generation (GitHub Actions release.yml).
- `backend/installer/` — Installer generators: shell, PowerShell, Homebrew, npm, MSI, macOS .pkg.
- `backend/templates.rs` — Minijinja template engine. Templates in `cargo-dist/templates/`.
- `announce.rs` — Release notes and changelog handling.
- `sign/` — Code signing (macOS, SSL.com).
- `manifest.rs` — dist-manifest.json generation.

## Testing

- Uses `insta` for snapshot tests. After `cargo test`, run `cargo insta review`.
- Tests are stateful and CANNOT run in parallel. Do NOT use nextest.
- Mock builds via `build::fake` module.
- Test fixtures in `axoproject/tests/projects/`.

## Key Commands

- Build: `cargo build`
- Test: `cargo test` then `cargo insta review`
- Lint: `cargo clippy --workspace`
- Format: `cargo fmt --all`
- Typos: `typos`

